result.execSummary:
The defendant Bryan K. Houston was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

records.addlTxt: 14CM-494, 15CF-163 and 16CF-41 - All Cases Called @ 1:45 PM: Defendant Bryan K. Houston in court with attorney Jeanne Lila Zamzow, both appearing in person.  Defendant Bryan K. Houston in custody.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Parties admit receipt of PSI Report and no material errors found or offered.  Victim as to 14CM-494 present and makes a statement to the Court.  Victim as to 16CF-41 present and makes statement to the Court.  Argument by DA - stipulation as to SEH credit and recited.  62 days as to TS 15CF-163 and 133 days TS as to 16CF-41.  No TS credit as to 14CM-494 - Deferred SEH agreement.  Atty Zamzow confirms Stip on TS credit.  Argument by DA - argues for slight deviation from DOC's recommendation on prison sentence.  Argument by Atty Zamzow - her recommendation for SEH would result in Def's time being served in Co Jail rather than prison term.  Statement by Defendant:  Yes.  The Court:  Placing Def on probation would unduly depreciate the pattern of behavior and has considered PSI as authored.  15CF-163 (OWI 5) Ct 1:  4 yrs/ 6 mos term of imprisonment - bifurcated as 18 mos IC/3 yrs ES with 62 days TS credit.  16CF-41 (Fel BJump) Ct 5:  4 yr/6 mos term of imprisonment concurrent to 15CF-163 - 18 mos IC/3 yr ES - with 133 TS credit.  16CF-41 - Cts 1 and 2 - S/W 1 yr probation which will be consecutive to SEH imposed in 15CF163 and 16CF-41.   14CM-494: Court Costs only - 60 DTP.  Conditions of ES:  AODA and any follow thru as recommended;  the defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician; No Contact with:  D. Ennis; E. Verburgt; A Hansen; T Hansen and/or D. Rhode; Rest of $654.18  ($18.83 to D. Rhode and Balance to A. Hansen $635.35) DOC authorized to collect from wages and any other funds in account as per guidelines;  comply with any other terms or conditions of ES or probation as established by Agent; DNA sample and surcharge ordered by the Court.  Right to expungement of DNA through the Dept of Justice explained. Conditions of ES apply to both felony cases and the 2 misd offenses in 16CF-41.  Costs in 14CM494 file will not include any DNA sample or surcharge.  15CF-163:  36 mos DL Rev/IID/OWI Assessment prior to relicenses; fine inclusive of costs of $2500; $42.50 blood draw fee.  60 DTP or PP - all bonds to be applied.  Def is found eligible for SAP and CIP.  Appeal Rights Given.
